  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two blocks &nbsp;labeled Block 1 and Block 2 located on a horizonal surface. There is a vertical wall to the left of the horizontal surface. Block 1 is larger than Block 2, and is being pulled away from the wall by a horizontal string.&nbsp;Block 2, which is smaller than Block 1 and lies on top of Block 1, &nbsp;is being held at rest by a string attached to the wall.\" src=\"/images/b05e794173cef423967cee0ce4d9976e.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3.0 kilograms\"><math alttext=\"3.0 kilograms\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3.0</mn><mtext> kg</mtext></math></span></span> is on a horizontal surface and is pulled at a constant velocity to the right by a string, as shown in the figure. Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.0 kilgram\"><math alttext=\"1.0 kilgram\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>kg</mtext></math></span></span> is on Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and held at rest by another string attached to a vertical wall. The coefficients of kinetic and static friction between all surfaces are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.20\"><math alttext=\"0.20\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.20</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.40\"><math alttext=\"0.40\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.40</mn></math></span></span>, respectively, and the strings have negligible mass. What is the tension in the string attached to Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
